{
  "texts": [
    "The common way this is done in the literature is as follows: we start by considering the WZW model on Euclidean AdS 3 (denoted by H + 3 = SL(2; C)/SU(2)) [21,22].",
    "The bosonic part of the action in first order form is given byS = k 4π d 2 z (4∂Φ ∂Φ + β∂γ + β ∂γ -e -2Φ β β),(2.17)where Φ → ∞ is at the boundary of H + 3 and (γ, γ) are complex coordinates that represent coordinates on S 2 when we are at large Φ.",
    "The equations of motion fix β = e 2Φ ∂γ and β = e 2Φ ∂γ.",
    "We may add a Fradkin-Tseytlin term, coupling to the dilaton Φ [32,47], see appendix C. This gives the revised action [21] S AdS 3 = k 4π d 2 z 4∂Φ ∂Φ + β∂γ + β ∂γ -e -2Φ β β - 1 k RΦ, (2.18)with R the worldsheet Ricci scalar.",
    "We should point out, however, that at the level of the path integral these two actions are only equivalent if the path integral is dominated by large Φ contributions [22]."
  ]
}